Sentencas: Proton-conducting solid-oxide fuel cell (H-SOFC) is an alternative promising low-temperature electrochemical cell for renewable energy, but the performance is insufficient because of the low activity of cathode materials at low temperatures.
Titulo: Promoted Performance of Layered Perovskite PrBaFe2O5+δ Cathode for Protonic Ceramic Fuel Cells by Zn Doping

Sentencas: A layered perovskite oxide PrBaFe1.9Zn0.1O5+delta (PBFZ) was synthesized and investigated as a promising cathode material for low-temperature H-SOFC.
Titulo: Promoted Performance of Layered Perovskite PrBaFe2O5+δ Cathode for Protonic Ceramic Fuel Cells by Zn Doping

Sentencas: Here, the partial substitution of Fe by Zn further enhances the electrical conductivity and thermal compatibility of PrBaFe2O5+delta (PBF).
Titulo: Promoted Performance of Layered Perovskite PrBaFe2O5+δ Cathode for Protonic Ceramic Fuel Cells by Zn Doping

Sentencas: The PBFZ exhibits improved conductivity in the air at intermediate temperatures and good chemical compatibility with electrolytes.
Titulo: Promoted Performance of Layered Perovskite PrBaFe2O5+δ Cathode for Protonic Ceramic Fuel Cells by Zn Doping

Sentencas: The oxygen vacancy formed at the PBFZ lattice due to Zn doping enhances proton defects, resulting in an improved performance by extending the catalytic sites to the whole cathode area.
Titulo: Promoted Performance of Layered Perovskite PrBaFe2O5+δ Cathode for Protonic Ceramic Fuel Cells by Zn Doping

Sentencas: A single cell with a Ni-BZCY anode, PBFZ cathode, and BaZr0.7Ce0.2Y0.1O3-delta (BZCY) electrolyte membrane was successfully fabricated and tested at 550-700 degrees C.
Titulo: Promoted Performance of Layered Perovskite PrBaFe2O5+δ Cathode for Protonic Ceramic Fuel Cells by Zn Doping

Sentencas: The maximum power density and R-p were enhanced to 513 mW center dot cm(-2) and 0.3 omega center dot cm(2) at 700 degrees C, respectively, due to Zn doping.
Titulo: Promoted Performance of Layered Perovskite PrBaFe2O5+δ Cathode for Protonic Ceramic Fuel Cells by Zn Doping
